======================================
             SSM LIBRARY
   INSTALATION, COMPILATION RUNNING
=====================================

=====================
I) INSTALATION
=====================

1) Load modules
---------------
source setup_lrz.sh       on LRZ cluster (SLURM)
source setup_brutus.sh    on Brutus, Euler
---------------
(versions used: open_mpi/1.4.5, boost/1.49.0, python/2.7.2, gcc/4.4.6, blitz/0.9.3, java/1.6.0_31)


2) Get and configure SBML
* from http://sourceforge.net/projects/sbml/files/libsbml/
* tested with version libSBML-5.8.0 (libSBML-5.8.0-core-plus-packages-src.zip)
* installation notes: http://sbml.org/Special/Software/libSBML/3.4.1/docs/java-api/libsbml-installation.html#SWIG
--------------------------
cd $HOME
mkdir sbml-libs 
mv libSBML-5.8.0-core-plus-packages-src.zip sbml-libs
unzip libSBML-5.8.0-core-plus-packages-src.zip
cd usr/libSBML-5.8.0-Source
./configure --with-expat --with-python --with-java --prefix="$HOME/sbml-libs"
-------------------------

NOTE: If above configuration fails, configure with SWIG (needed for LRZ cluster)

2.1) Configuration of SWIG:
* Download SWIG:http://www.swig.org/download.html
* Important: libSBML is known to work with SWIG version 1.3.33 or later
* Tested version: swig-3.0.12

-------------------
mv swig-3.0.12 sbml-libs
cd swig-3.0.12
./configure --prefix=$HOME/sbml-libs/swig-3.0.12
make
make install
-------------------

2.2) Configure SBML with SWIG
-------------------
cd $HOME/sbml-libs/usr/libSBML-5.8.0-Source
./configure --with-expat --with-python --with-java --with-swig="$HOME/sbml-libs/swig-3.0.12" --prefix="$HOME/sbml-libs"
make 
make install
-------------------






compile2.sh	compile script for brutus
link2.sh	link script for brutus



- libexpat, blitz and boost available from brutus
- adapt compile2.sh and link2.sh (to change "$HOME/more_lib" if needed)
- Compile SSM with "./compile2.sh && ./link2.sh"
- USAGE: ./StochasticSimulationMethods <SBMLFILE>
-> generate sbml files (.xml) with MATLAB codes

